# Testing and verification

- Look for existing tests before adding new ones.
- Add or update tests for changed behaviour, bug fixes, and edge cases.
- Prefer focused tests close to the changed code over broad end-to-end tests unless the change crosses system boundaries.
- Include at least one regression test for bug fixes when practical.
- Run the narrowest relevant test first, then broader checks if available.
- Do not weaken, delete, or skip tests to make the suite pass unless the task explicitly asks for test maintenance.
- If a test is flaky or impossible to run locally, document the reason and what validation was performed instead.

Common validation commands to discover from the repo:
- package scripts in package.json
- Makefile targets
- CI workflows under .github/workflows
- project-specific test, typecheck, lint, build, and format commands
